# AGENTS.md

> Project: **{{PROJECT_NAME}}** — coordinated via [Codepakt](https://codepakt.com)

## Prerequisites
- Install: `npm i -g codepakt`
- Start server: `cpk server start` (runs on port 41920)
- Dashboard: http://localhost:41920

## Workflow (follow exactly)

All output is JSON. Parse it programmatically.

```bash
# 1. Check assigned tasks
cpk task mine --agent <your-name>

# 2. Pick up next available task
cpk task pickup --agent <your-name>

# 3. Read task details
cpk task show T-001

# 4. Do the work

# 5. Mark complete
cpk task done T-001 --agent <your-name> --notes "what you did"

# 6. If blocked
cpk task block T-001 --agent <your-name> --reason "why"

# 7. Create tasks (command is 'add', NOT 'create')
cpk task add --title "Fix bug" --priority P0
cpk task add --title "Feature" --priority P1 --epic "Auth" --depends-on T-001

# 8. Update any field directly
cpk task update T-001 --status open   # Change status
cpk task update T-001 --priority P0   # Change priority
cpk task update T-001 --assignee dev  # Reassign

# 9. Other useful commands
cpk task list                        # All tasks
cpk task list --status open           # Filter by status
cpk task unblock T-001               # Remove block
cpk board status                     # Board health
cpk docs search "topic"              # Search knowledge base
```

## Task Lifecycle
backlog → open → in-progress → **done** (dependencies resolve immediately)
`task done` goes straight to done — no review gate. Review is optional (human-managed).

## Important
- Command is `task add` — NOT `task create`
- `--agent` is required on: `task pickup`, `task done`, `task block`, `task mine`
- Alternative: `export CPK_AGENT=<your-name>` to skip `--agent` each time
- Every command needs a subcommand: `cpk board status` (NOT `cpk board`)
- Server must be running: `cpk server start` (check with `cpk server status`)

